        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 13 at 5:30PM EDT until July 13 at 6:30PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>SVRBGM

The National Weather Service in Binghamton has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Oneida County in central New York...
North central Madison County in central New York...

* Until 630 PM EDT.

* At 530 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Verona Beach,
or near Oneida, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Rome, Oneida, Lee, Verona, Westmoreland, Vienna, Canastota,
Trenton, Floyd, and Whitesboro.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Heavy rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to flash
flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
